---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import Comments from '../../../components/Comments.astro';
---

<Layout title="Lists - Markdown Tutorial" description="Learn how to create ordered and unordered lists in Markdown." lang="en">
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="section section-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-[var(--color-terracotta)] mb-4">
            Basic Syntax / Lists
          </p>
          <h1 class="font-serif-display text-[var(--text-inverse)] mb-6">Lists</h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-[var(--text-on-dark)] opacity-80" style="line-height: 1.6;">
            Organize items into ordered or unordered lists to make information structured and readable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container max-w-4xl">
        <div class="prose">
          <h2>Unordered Lists</h2>
          <p>To create an unordered list, add dashes (-), asterisks (*), or plus signs (+) in front of each item:</p>
          <pre><code>{`- First item
- Second item
- Third item
- Fourth item`}</code></pre>

          <h2>Ordered Lists</h2>
          <p>To create an ordered list, add numbers followed by periods before each item:</p>
          <pre><code>{`1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item
4. Fourth item`}</code></pre>

          <h2>Nested Lists</h2>
          <p>Indent one or more items to create nested lists:</p>
          <pre><code>{`- Fruit
  - Apple
  - Banana
- Vegetables
  1. Tomato
  2. Cucumber`}</code></pre>

          <h2>Best Practices</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Numbers don't need to be in sequential order</li>
            <li>Lists should start with number 1</li>
            <li>Don't mix different delimiters in the same list</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Comments slug="basic-lists" />
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
